--> Interpreter 
---- translates one statement at a time into machine code.
---- interpreter needed everytime
---- Partial execution till error occurs
---- easy to use



--> Compiler 
---- scans entire program and translates whole of it into machine code
---- compiler is not required once compiled
---- no execution if error occurs
---- not as easy as compiler



----> Java is a hybrid(interpreter + compiler) language

----> How Java Works?
		Java is compiled into the byte code(class file) and then it is interpreted to Machine code.
		
		Source Code ----------------------> Byte code -----------------------------> Machine Code
						 Compiled							   Interpreted